    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou1/sensitivity-analysis",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "COU1 hemolysis sensitivity to mesh density and blood viscosity",
    "description": "Mesh density was varied across three refinement levels (coarse 1.2M, medium 3.8M, fine 9.1M cells) and blood dynamic viscosity was perturbed ±15% around the nominal Newtonian value of 0.0035 Pa·s. The relative hemolysis index (RH) varied by less than 4.2% across mesh levels and by less than 6.8% across the viscosity range, confirming that the QoI is insensitive to these parameters at the assessed operating points and that the medium mesh is sufficient for MRL 2 requirements."
  },
  "hasContextOfUse": {
